row.question: In a city, 20% of the population travels by car, 50% travels by bus and 10% travels by both car and bus. Then, the percentage of the population that travels by either car or bus is...
row.rationale:
According to the problem,
p(car)=20%=1/5
p(bus)=50%=1/2
p(car ∩ bus)=10%=1/10
Since p(car u bus)=p(car)+p(bus)-p(car n bus)
p(car ∪ bus)=1/5 + 1/2 - 1/10=3/5=60%
ANSWER:C
